<Layout title="Courses — Chan Nirak Choun" currentPage="courses">

  <h1>Courses</h1>

  <p class="section-intro">
    I got inspired by Scott Young's MIT Challenge, where he completed MIT's four-year computer science
    curriculum in twelve months using freely available courseware, and his book <em>Ultralearning</em>.
    That led me to start putting together my own self-directed curriculum. Most of the courses listed
    here were found through <a href="https://csdiy.wiki/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">csdiy.wiki</a>,
    a community-driven guide to self-learning CS with courses from universities like MIT, UC Berkeley,
    Stanford, and CMU. I use these to supplement my formal education with hands-on projects and deeper
    theoretical foundations than what a single degree program can cover.
  </p>

